Create a procedure  without parameters to display student marks above 50.

Create a procedure to get input for student id and display that student details.

Create a procedure to get input for student id and output as student name.

CREATE PROCEDURE GetStudentsAbove50
AS
BEGIN
    SELECT *
    FROM Students
    WHERE Marks > 50;
END;
EXEC GetStudentsAbove50;
CREATE PROCEDURE GetStudentName
    @StudentID INT,
    @StudentName VARCHAR(50) OUTPUT
AS
BEGIN
    SELECT @StudentName = Name
    FROM Students
    WHERE StudentID = @StudentID;
END;
